title: The ‘hypocritical’ left stays silent whilst ‘teenagers are butchered in Iranian streets’
description: Israeli Journalist Emily Schrader calls out the left’s hypocrisy by holding protests supporting the Islamic Republic of Iran.  “What we have seen is several events, particularly in the UK, organised by the Anti-Israel movement that supports the Islamic Republic of Iran,” Ms Schrader told Sky News host Danica De Giorgio.   “When it comes to even teenagers being butchered in the streets by the Islamic Republic, complete silence.”

title: Race Discrimination Commissioner says Australia Day has been ‘co-opted by white supremacists’
description: Sky News host Danica De Giorgio criticises Race Discrimination Commissioner Giridharan Sivaraman.  “I really hate being told Australia is a racist country,” Ms De Giorgio said.   “What a horrible person you must be if you love your country.”

title: World’s Gone Mad: ‘Deranged’ Trevor Noah’s Donald Trump joke falls flat
description: Sky News host Rowan Dean blasts Grammys host Trevor Noah as “deranged” after a joke referencing US President Donald Trump and Jeffrey Epstein fell flat.

title: 'A really bad government’: The Coalition need to ‘fight the real enemy’
description: Nationals MP Michael McCormack believes the Coalition needs to get back together to fight the Albanese government.   “The Nationals and Liberals need to get back together for not just our own sakes but for the sake of the nation,” Mr McCormack told Sky News host Danica De Giorgio.  “It has to happen eventually.  “We can’t go into an election divorced or separated. We simply can’t.  “To remain separate means that we fight amongst ourselves rather than fighting the real enemy, and that is a really bad government.  “People aren’t feeling safe and secure in their own homes.”

title: Jacinta Price is ‘sick to death’ of the grievance industry causing division and resentment
description: Liberal Senator Jacinta Nampijinpa Price criticises the way many Australians are portrayed and the impact the grievance industry is having on Australian culture.  “Every day Australians are at the moment sick of being portrayed in a particular way,” Ms Price told Sky News host Danica De Giorgio.  “There are a lot of Australians who are deeply proud of who we are as a country, of our heritage, of our history, of what we have built together as Australians.  “I am utterly sick to death of the grievance industry.”

title: A ‘smug’ Albanese turns the Liberals and Nationals into ‘a comedy skit’
description: Sky News host Danica De Giorgio criticises the Coalition for not putting pressure on the Albanese government.  “Now 2028 is a long way off, but the Coalition divorce only seeks to bolster One Nation even further,” Ms De Giorgio said.  “It works for the always smug Anthony Albanese, who turned question time into a comedy skit this week, with the Liberals and Nationals the punchline.  “There is no heat on this PM, despite him presiding over rising inflation and a rate rise this week.”

title: ‘Imagine the outcry’: Backlash over Labour’s push to make countryside ‘less White
description: Sky News host Danica De Giorgio condemns the UK Labour government for their nationwide diversity drive to make the countryside “less White”.  “One of the recommendations includes keeping dogs under stricter control because some migrants are scared of them,” Ms De Giorgio said.  “Imagine if it were a drive to make the countryside less Black or Asian, can you imagine the outcry?” ​

title: ‘It’s not inclusion it’s embarrassment’: Outrage over claims the countryside is ‘too White’
description: ‘Triggered with Samara Gill’ host Samara Gill blasts the UK Labour government over claims the countryside has a problem with being “too White”.  “The English countryside wasn’t designed by a focus group in Westminster. It wasn’t curated by a DEI officer,” Ms Gill told Sky News host Danica De Giorgio.  “Now the solution, we’re told, is to rebrand it … even suggestions that pubs! Yes pubs! Might be culturally off-putting.  “What’s really going on here isn’t inclusion. It’s embarrassing. It’s a deep, bureaucratic discomfort with anything that looks unmistakably English and unapologetically traditional.”

title: Sky News host explodes: ‘I’ve had enough’ of apologies, hypocrisy and being afraid to speak
description: Sky News host Rowan Dean has had enough of apology culture, the hypocritical left, and institutions ruining Australia.  “I have had enough of being told that my homeland, my birthright, does not belong to me,” Mr Dean said.  “I've had enough of apologies.  “Since when did going multicultural mean giving up the things we loved?  “I've had enough of the hypocrisy, the humbug and the self-hatred that festers in this country.”

title: Comedian brilliantly impersonates Donald Trump if he were Australian
description: Sky News host James Morrow laughs at comedian Scott Miller’s impression of US President Donald Trump if he were Australian.  “Have you ever thought about what Donald Trump would sound like if he were Australian?” Mr Morrow said.  “Well, comedian Scott Miller has, and here’s the result.”

title: Anthony Albanese greeted with grand ceremony in Jakarta
description: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese has arrived at Jakarta’s presidential palace, where he was greeted by a grand ceremonial welcome.  Mr Albanese is in Indonesia to sign a historic security agreement between Australia and Indonesia.  There are no expenses being spared for this welcoming party.  Behind all the ceremonial welcome is the signing of what Prime Minister Albanese believes is a watershed security agreement to bring Australia and Indonesia closer together and to align their thinking when it comes to the many challenges they face when it comes to regional security.

title: Epstein file ‘cover up’ has been used to ‘protect’ the elites
description: Political Commentator Stephanie Hamill says people exposed in the Epstein files must be “held accountable”.  Ms Hamill told Sky News host James Morrow that there’s been a “cover-up” of the files.  “In an effort to protect all of these people.”

title: US midterms may be ‘closer’ than people assume
description: Sky News host James Morrow says things are “closer” than people may assume for the US midterm elections.  Mr Morrow said recent polling has shown US voters evenly split between Democrat and Republican.  “In a generic political ballot where likely voters, not registered voters … the Democrats only have a slight advantage.”

title: ‘Insane’: Democrats nonstop calling Republicans a ‘threat’ to democracy
description: Americans for Fair Treatment Senior Fellow Corey DeAngelis says the Democrats are acting “insane”.  Mr DeAngelis told Sky News host James Morrow that Democrats are calling Republicans a “threat to democracy”.  “Every chance that they can get.”

title: Democrats fighting to ‘get in power’ in any way possible
description: Americans for Fair Treatment Senior Fellow Corey DeAngelis says the Democrats are fighting to “try to get in power”.  Mr DeAngelis told Sky News host James Morrow that they are doing it “however they can”.  “They don’t care about our constitution, they don’t care about the rule of law, and they certainly don’t care about having voting rights actually mean something.”
